Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: Called at 3:24 PM. Also called 13CF238, 13CM253, 13CM230 and 14CF20. Dean Frank appears in person and in custody with counsel Jeff Joy. State appears by Charles Simono. State - have resolution on all matters - defendant would plead G per the signed plea questionnaire to the following counts: 13CF157 - counts #3 and #4; 13CF238 - counts #2 and #3, 14CF20 - G to only count; DRI following counts: 13CF157 - counts #1, #2 and #5, 13CF238 - counts #1, #4 and #5, 13CM230 - all counts, 13CM253 - only count. Frank and Joy agree. Court dismisses counts as previously stated. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. Frank understands the right he is giving up by pleading today. State has complied with victim notification requirements and states cases that would apply to notification - did provide court with victim impact statement to all parties on 13CM230 and the victim in 13CF238 has been non-responsive - makes final argument prior to sentencing - recommends the following: 13CF238 - count #2 - 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of extended supervsion, #3 - 9 months in jail to be served in prison confinement - concurrent to count #2; 13CF157 - counts #3 and #4 - 6 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of extended supervision - stayed - place on probation for 5 years, concurrent to prison time on 13CF238 and concurrent to each other; 14CF20 - 1 year in WI State Prison System, concurrent to prison time on 13CF238; cannot avail himself of any early release program that is in effect now or while incarcerated except for the 80% time component, conditions left to P&P/prison agent(s), not asking for any fines - leave up to discretion of the court, requires costs and possible surcharges would apply. Joy makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - no objection to costs but would prefer no fines for stated reasons (child support) - no credit as he was revoked. State responds. Frank makes statement, remorseful. Court sentences the defendant to the following: 13CF238 - 6 years in the WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of extended supervsion, costs & DNA conditions absolute sobriety #3 - 9 months in jail to be served in prison confinement - concurrent to count, costs #2; 13CF157 - counts #3costs and DNA and #4 costs - 6 years in WI State Prison System consisting of 3 years of initial confinement followed by 3 years of extended supervision - stayed - place on probation for 5 years, concurrent to prison time on 13CF238 and concurrent to each other 14CF20 1 year jail concurrent to all other things with costs and DNA costs. Appeal rights given
Pre-trial conference on June 5, 2014 at 03:00 pm.
Pre-trial conference on May 13, 2014 at 11:00 am.

records.addlTxt: Called at 11:04 AM. Also called 13CF238, 13CM253, 14CF20 and 13CM230. Dean Frank appears in person and in custody without counsel. State appears by Charles Simono. Court - 13CM230 - what is status of case. State not sure. Frank now wants an attorney on that case (13CM230). Court will set this matter for STC. State - bond - no contact with Una Ross or any of the children involved in that family - $500 signature bond. Court so orders, no consumption of alcohol and no contact with Una Ross or their children. Court - 14CF20 - reads charges and penalties. Frank wants an attorney on all matters, can afford his own - needs at least one week. Court - 13CM253 - reads charges and penalties and right to attorney. Court - 13CF238 - reads charges and penalties - Jeff Joy now appears telephonically (11:11 AM). Court informs Joy of what has already been put on the record. Joy states he will appear specially today, has not officially been retained. Frank has no objections to the special appearance. State - 13CM253 - $500 signature bond, no objections, so ordered with no consumption of alcohol. Cout - 14CF20 - State - $2000 cash, no objections. Court - $2000 cash - Joy will waive time limits on all matters, court sets all CF cases for PH on 4/23/14 at 3:00 PM. 13CF238 - court reads charges and penalties. State - 13CF238 - ask for $75,000 cash. Joy objects - ask for more like $10,000 cash for stated reasons. State responds. Frank states he will not be arguing on any bonds requested by the State. Court - 13CF238 - $25,000.00 - no contact with Sarah Pospychalla, no consumption of alcohol, no contact thru 940.47 court order and State to prepare that paperwork. 13CF157 - Court reads charges and penalties. State - bond - $75,000.00 with same conditions as 13CF238. Joy renews his objection. Court - bond - $50,000.00 cash with same conditions and State to prepare paperwork for 940.47 provision.
Preliminary hearing on April 23, 2014 at 03:00 pm.
Initial appearance on March 26, 2014 at 10:00 am.
